        </prov>
        <crosshead id="DLM1584794" toc="yes">Miscellaneous offences</crosshead>
        <prov id="DLM1584795" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">136</label>
          <heading>Offence of false declaration, etc, in support of application for authorisation or grant of QFE status</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person (<emphasis style="bold">A</emphasis>) commits an offence if A has, for the purpose of obtaining authorisation or the grant of QFE status, either for A or for any other person,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>either orally or in writing, made any declaration or representation knowing it to be false or misleading in a material particular; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>produced to the Commission or made use of any document knowing it to contain a declaration or representation referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz">paragraph (a)</citation>; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>produced to the Commission or made use of any document knowing that it was not genuine.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person who commits an offence under this section is liable on summary conviction to a fine,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in the case of an individual, not exceeding $100,000:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>in the case of an entity, not exceeding $300,000.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM1584796" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">137</label>
          <heading>Failure to comply with summons by Commissioner to attend disciplinary committee hearing</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person summoned under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282643" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637406 - prov 109" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637642" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 109</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785488" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637642" atidlm:targetKey="13497002" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584764" atidlm:targetName="prov 109" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637642" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584747.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584768.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584796" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> commits an offence if he or she, without sufficient cause,—</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>fails to attend in accordance with the summons; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not give evidence when required to do so; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not give evidence under oath when required to do so; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not answer any question that is lawfully asked by the disciplinary committee; or</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>does not provide any documents, things, or information that the summons requires the person to provide.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person who commits an offence under this section is liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding $5,000.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>A person must not be convicted of an offence under this section if witnesses' fees, allowances, and expenses to which the person is entitled under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282644" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637407 - prov 111" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637643" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 111</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785489" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637643" atidlm:targetKey="13497004" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584766" atidlm:targetName="prov 111" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637643" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584747.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584768.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584796" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> have not been paid or tendered to him or her.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <cf>2005 No 38 s 35</cf>
        </prov>
      </subpart>
    </part>
    <part date.instructed="2007-08-03" id="DLM1584797" in.amend="false" instructing.office="Economic Development" irdnumbering="no" toc="yes" date.first.valid="2099-09-09" act.no="91" act.type="public" date.as.at="2008-09-27" date.assent="2008-09-27" stage="not-in-force" year="2008">
      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
      <heading>General provisions</heading>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584798" toc="yes">Appeal of decisions</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584799" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">138</label>
        <heading>Right of appeal</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>A person affected may appeal to a District Court against any decision of—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the Commission to—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>decline authorisation under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282645" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637408 - prov 55" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637644" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 55(4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785490" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637644" atidlm:targetKey="13496204" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584696" atidlm:targetName="prov 55" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637644" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584691.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>decline QFE status under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282646" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637409 - prov 67" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637645" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 67(4)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785491" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637645" atidlm:targetKey="13496404" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584710" atidlm:targetName="prov 67" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637645" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584705.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>: or</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>take any action referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282647" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637411 - prov 59" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637646" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 59(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785492" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637646" atidlm:targetKey="13496209" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584701" atidlm:targetName="prov 59" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637646" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584691.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> or <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282648" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637412 - prov 71" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637647" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>71(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785493" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637647" atidlm:targetKey="13496409" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584715" atidlm:targetName="prov 71" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637647" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584705.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iv</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>give a direction under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282649" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637413 - prov 61" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637648" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 61</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785494" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637648" atidlm:targetKey="13496211" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584703" atidlm:targetName="prov 61" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637648" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584691.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> or <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282650" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637414 - prov 73" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637649" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>73</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785495" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637649" atidlm:targetKey="13496411" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584717" atidlm:targetName="prov 73" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637649" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584705.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>; or</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the disciplinary committee to take any action referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282651" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637415 - prov 101" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637650" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 101(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785496" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637650" atidlm:targetKey="13497014" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584755" atidlm:targetName="prov 101" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637650" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584747.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584799" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> or (5)</citation>.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>An appeal—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>must be brought to the District Court by way of notice of appeal in accordance with the rules of court; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>must be lodged within 20 working days after notice of the decision is communicated to the appellant, or within any further time a District Court Judge allows on application made before or after the period expires.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 38</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584800" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">139</label>
        <heading>Notice of right of appeal</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>When notifying a person under this Act of any decision against which <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282652" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637416 - prov 138" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637651" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 138</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785497" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637651" atidlm:targetKey="13497425" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584799" atidlm:targetName="prov 138" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637651" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584800" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> gives him or her a right of appeal, the Commission or the disciplinary committee must also notify the person in writing of the right of appeal and the time within which an appeal must be lodged.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 39</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584801" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">140</label>
        <heading>Decision to have effect pending determination of appeal</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>A decision against which an appeal is lodged under this Part continues in force unless the District Court orders otherwise.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 40</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584802" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">141</label>
        <heading>Procedure on appeal</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>An appeal under this Part must be heard as soon as is reasonably practicable after it is lodged.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>An appeal under this Part is by way of rehearing.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>On hearing the appeal, the District Court—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>may confirm, reverse, or modify the decision appealed against; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>may make any other decision that the person or body that made the decision appealed against could have made.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para>
              <text>The court must not review—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>any part of a decision not appealed against; or</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>any decision not appealed against at all.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 41</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584803" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">142</label>
        <heading>Court's decision final</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>Except as provided in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282653" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637417 - prov 146" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637652" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 146</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785498" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637652" atidlm:targetKey="13497433" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584807" atidlm:targetName="prov 146" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637652" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584803" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the decision of the District Court on an appeal under this Part is final.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 42</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584804" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">143</label>
        <heading>Court may refer matter back for reconsideration</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>Instead of determining an appeal under this Part, the District Court may direct the person or body whose decision is under appeal to reconsider, either generally or in respect of any specified aspect, the whole or any part of the decision.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>In giving a direction under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>, the court—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>must state its reasons for the direction; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>may give any other directions it thinks just in relation to the matter referred back for reconsideration.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>Upon being directed to reconsider a matter, the person or body whose decision is under appeal—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>must reconsider the matter; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>in doing so, must—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>take the court's reasons into account; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>give effect to the court's directions.</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 43</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584805" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">144</label>
        <heading>Orders as to costs</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>On an appeal under this Part, the District Court may order any party to the appeal to pay to any other party to the appeal any or all of the costs incurred by the other party in respect of the appeal.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 44</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584806" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">145</label>
        <heading>Orders as to publication of names</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>On any appeal under this Part, the District Court may, if in its opinion it is proper to do so, prohibit the publication of the name or particulars of the affairs of a financial adviser or any other person.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>In deciding whether to make an order under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>, the court must have regard to—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the interests of any person (including, without limitation, the privacy of any complainant); and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the public interest.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 45(1), (2)</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584807" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">146</label>
        <heading>Appeal on question of law</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>A party to an appeal under this Part may appeal to the High Court against any determination of law arising in the appeal.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The appeal must be heard and determined in accordance with the appropriate rules of court.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1283490" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1638162 - part 4 Appeals" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1638190" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Part 4</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="786092" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1638190" atidlm:targetKey="2043201" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM312656" atidlm:targetName="part 4 Appeals" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1638190" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM312656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584807" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> of the Summary Proceedings Act 1957 (together with the other provisions of that Act that are applied in that Part) applies to the appeal—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>so far as it is applicable and with all necessary modifications; but</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>only so far as it relates to appeals on questions of law.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz">Subsection (3)</citation> overrides <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (2)</citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>2005 No 38 s 46</cf>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584808" toc="yes">Securities Commission: general powers</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584809" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">147</label>
        <heading>Commission may exercise powers under Securities Act 1978</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may exercise any of its powers under the Securities Act 1978 in performing its functions under this Act.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1283410" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637681 - part 3 General investigation and enforcement powers" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1638110" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>Part 3</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785810" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1638110" atidlm:targetKey="135200" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM29717" atidlm:targetName="part 3 General investigation and enforcement powers" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1638110" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM29717.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584809" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> of the Securities Act 1978 applies to the exercise by the Commission of any of its powers under the Securities Act 1978 in the performance of its functions under this Act.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 44</cf>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584810" toc="yes">Exemptions</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584811" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">148</label>
        <heading>Commission may grant exemptions</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>Subject to <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (2)</citation>, the Commission may, in its discretion and on the terms and conditions (if any) that it thinks fit, by notice in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis> exempt any person or class of persons, any transaction or class of transactions, or any class of financial advice (for example, financial advice given by telephone) from compliance with a disclosure obligation or obligations.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission must be satisfied, before it grants an exemption, that the cost of compliance with the disclosure obligation would—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>be unreasonable; or</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>not be justified by the benefit of compliance.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584812" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">149</label>
        <heading>Commission must notify reasons for exemption</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission’s reasons for granting an exemption (including why the exemption is appropriate) must be notified in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis> with the exemption.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>However, the Commission may defer notifying or not notify the reasons for granting an exemption if the Commission is satisfied that it is proper to do so on the ground of commercial confidentiality.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 48A</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584813" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">150</label>
        <heading>Commission may vary or revoke exemption </heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may vary the exemption in the same way as it may grant the exemption under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282654" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637418 - prov 148" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637653" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 148</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785499" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637653" atidlm:targetKey="13497410" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584811" atidlm:targetName="prov 148" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637653" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584813" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may revoke the exemption by notice in the <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 48B</cf>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584814" toc="yes">Information sharing</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584815" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">151</label>
        <heading>Information sharing</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may communicate to any of the agencies referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (4)</citation> any information that the Commission—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>holds in relation to the exercise of the Commission's powers, or the performance of its functions and duties, under this Act; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>considers may assist the agency in the exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions and duties.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may use any information communicated to it by an agency referred to in <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (4)</citation> in the exercise of the Commission's powers, or the performance of its functions and duties, under this Act.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>This section applies no matter what any enactment, contract, deed, or document may say.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para>
              <text>The agencies to which this section applies are the following:</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the Registrar:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the Commerce Commission:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the New Zealand Police:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                <para>
                  <text>an approved dispute resolution scheme:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                <para>
                  <text>a licensing authority listed in <citation jurisdiction="nz">Schedule 2</citation> of the FSP Act:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">f</label>
                <para>
                  <text>an overseas regulator.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Commission may impose any conditions in relation to communicating information to an agency to which this section applies, including (without limitation) conditions relating to—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>maintaining the confidentiality of the information (in particular, information that is personal information within the meaning of the Privacy Act 1993):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the storing of, use of, or access to the information:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para>
                  <text>the copying, returning, or disposing of the information:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                <para>
                  <text>payment of the costs incurred by the Commission in communicating the information.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584816" toc="yes">Fees and levies</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584817" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">152</label>
        <heading>Commission's fees, charges, and costs</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>Regulations may be made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282655" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637419 - prov 155" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637654" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 155</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785500" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637654" atidlm:targetKey="13497421" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584822" atidlm:targetName="prov 155" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637654" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584817" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> for the payment to the Commission of fees, charges, and costs.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>If regulations have been made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282656" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637420 - prov 155" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637655" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 155(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785501" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637655" atidlm:targetKey="13497421" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584822" atidlm:targetName="prov 155" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637655" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584817" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> authorising the Commission to do so, the Commission may require payment of any costs incurred by the Commission.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584818" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">153</label>
        <heading>Operational levy</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Governor-General may, by Order in Council made on the recommendation of the Commission, impose on every authorised financial adviser and every QFE an operational levy of any amount for the purpose of funding the costs arising from the performance of any or all of the functions and duties under this Act of the Commission, the Commissioner, the code committee, or the disciplinary committee.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>A levy made under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation> may do either or both of the following:</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribe different amounts as the levy payable by different classes of authorised financial adviser or QFE:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>exempt from any liability to pay that levy, in whole or in part, any class or classes of authorised financial adviser or QFE, and may provide for the waiver or refund of the whole or part of that levy.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>Every levy imposed under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>  is payable, and recoverable as a debt due, to the Commission.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584819" toc="yes">Regulations</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584820" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">154</label>
        <heading>General regulations</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Governor-General may, by Order in Council made on the recommendation of the Minister in accordance with <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsections (3) and (4)</citation>, make regulations—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>defining the meaning of <emphasis style="bold">call debt security</emphasis> (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282657" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637421 - prov 5" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637656" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 5</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785502" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637656" atidlm:targetKey="13495206" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584508" atidlm:targetName="prov 5" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637656" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584505.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>specifying a product as a category 1 product (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 5</citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para>
                  <text>specifying a product as a category 2 product (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 5</citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing an entity for the purposes of the definition of trust account (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 5</citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                <para>
                  <text>for the purpose of determining when a person does not perform a financial adviser service under<citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282658" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637422 - prov 12" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637657" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent> section 12</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785503" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637657" atidlm:targetKey="13495604" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584647" atidlm:targetName="prov 12" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637657" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584642.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, specifying a person or class of persons and the circumstances in which they do not perform a financial adviser service:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">f</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the information that must be disclosed by an authorised financial adviser and the form of an authorised financial adviser’s disclosure statement (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282659" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637423 - prov 23" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637658" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>sections 23(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785504" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637658" atidlm:targetKey="13495812" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584660" atidlm:targetName="prov 23" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637658" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282660" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637424 - prov 24" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637659" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>24(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785505" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637659" atidlm:targetKey="13495813" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584661" atidlm:targetName="prov 24" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637659" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>): </text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">g</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the information that must be disclosed by a financial adviser performing a financial adviser service in relation to a category 2 product and the form of disclosure (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282661" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637425 - prov 25" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637660" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 25(2)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785506" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637660" atidlm:targetKey="13495814" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584662" atidlm:targetName="prov 25" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637660" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and (3)</citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">h</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the information that must be disclosed by a QFE and the form of disclosure (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282662" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637426 - prov 26" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637661" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 26(2)(a)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785507" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637661" atidlm:targetKey="13495815" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584663" atidlm:targetName="prov 26" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637661" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link> and (4)</citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing when, and subject to what terms and conditions, disclosure may be made in a joint disclosure document, and prescribing the form of a joint disclosure statement (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282663" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637427 - prov 31" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637662" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 31(3)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785508" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637662" atidlm:targetKey="13495820" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584668" atidlm:targetName="prov 31" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637662" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584656.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">j</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the form of an application for authorisation (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282664" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637428 - prov 53" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637663" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 53(a)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785509" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637663" atidlm:targetKey="13496202" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584694" atidlm:targetName="prov 53" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637663" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584691.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">k</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the form of an application for the grant of QFE status (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282665" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637429 - prov 65" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637664" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 65(a)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785510" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637664" atidlm:targetKey="13496402" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584708" atidlm:targetName="prov 65" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637664" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584705.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">l</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing information that must be contained in a QFE’s annual report (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282666" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637430 - prov 77" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637665" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 77(1)(f)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785511" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637665" atidlm:targetKey="13496417" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584723" atidlm:targetName="prov 77" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637665" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584705.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">m</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the procedure of the code committee (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282667" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637431 - prov 84" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637666" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 84(6)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785512" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637666" atidlm:targetKey="13496807" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584734" atidlm:targetName="prov 84" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637666" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584726.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">n</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the procedure of the disciplinary committee (<emphasis style="italic">see</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282668" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637432 - prov 106" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637667" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 106(5)</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785513" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637667" atidlm:targetKey="13497020" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584761" atidlm:targetName="prov 106" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637667" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584747.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584820" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>):</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">o</label>
                <para>
                  <text>providing for any other matters contemplated by this Act, necessary for its administration, or necessary for giving it full effect.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>In <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>, <def-term id="DLM1584821">prescribing the form</def-term> includes specifying additional content, means of communication, or any other requirement of form without necessarily specifying the use of a particular form.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Minister must consult with the Commission before making a recommendation under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Minister must not recommend regulations under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)(e)</citation> unless the Minister is satisfied that the person or persons to whom the regulations relate are engaged in an occupation that is subject to other regulation in New Zealand or overseas that is equivalent to regulation under this Act.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584822" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">155</label>
        <heading>Regulations relating to fees, charges, and costs</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Governor-General may from time to time, by Order in Council, make regulations—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>requiring the payment to the Commission of fees and charges—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>in connection with the performance by the Commission of any function or duty, or the exercise of any power, under this Act; or</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>on an application to the Commission to perform any function or duty, or exercise any power, under this Act; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the amounts of the fees and charges payable to the Commission; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prescribing the amount of any other fee required to be paid under this Act.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Governor-General may from time to time, by Order in Council, make regulations authorising the Commission to require payment to it of any costs incurred by the Commission in the performance by the Commission of any function or duty, or the exercise of any power, under this Act.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584823" toc="yes">Other matters</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584824" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">156</label>
        <heading>No contracting out</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>The provisions of this Act have effect no matter what any agreement may say.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 41V</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584825" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">157</label>
        <heading>Territorial scope</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para>
              <text>This Act applies to a financial adviser service performed in New Zealand by a person in New Zealand, regardless of where the person performing the financial adviser service is resident, is incorporated, or carries on business.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584826" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">158</label>
        <heading>Breach of exemption conditions</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>The breach of a term or condition of an exemption provided by regulations made under this Act or by notice under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282669" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637433 - prov 148" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637668" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 148</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785514" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637668" atidlm:targetKey="13497410" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584811" atidlm:targetName="prov 148" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637668" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584826" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is a breach of the obligation to which the exemption applies.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 49E</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584827" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">159</label>
        <heading>Exemption or regulation in respect of specified overseas jurisdictions</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="yes" denominator="yes"/>
            <para>
              <text>Without limiting <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1282670" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1637434 - prov 148" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1637669" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 148</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="intref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="785515" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1637669" atidlm:targetKey="13497410" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM1584811" atidlm:targetName="prov 148" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1637669" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584827" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, an exemption made under <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 148</citation> may extend, to all, or classes of, person, transaction, or other matters in relation to specified overseas jurisdictions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf> 1988 No 234 s 41V</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584828" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">160</label>
        <heading>Time for laying information for summary offences</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>Any information for an offence against this Act punishable on summary conviction may be laid at any time within 3 years after the date of the offence.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz">Subsection (1)</citation> applies despite <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1283491" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1638163 - prov 14" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1638191" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 14</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="786093" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1638191" atidlm:targetKey="2038878" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM311191" atidlm:targetName="prov 14" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1638191" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM311185.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584828" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> of, or anything else to the contrary in, the Summary Proceedings Act 1957.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <cf>1988 No 234 s 43U</cf>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM1584829" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">161</label>
        <heading>Ministry must review and report on operation of Act</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>The Ministry must, not later than 5 years after the commencement of this section,—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text>review the operation of this Act since the commencement of this section; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para>
                  <text>prepare a report on the review for the Minister.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The report on the review must include recommendations to the Minister on whether any amendments to the Act are necessary or desirable.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text>As soon as practicable after receiving the report, the Minister must present a copy of that report to the House of Representatives.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <crosshead id="DLM1584830" toc="yes">Other legislation affected</crosshead>
      <prov id="DLM1584831" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">162</label>
        <heading>KiwiSaver Act 2006 amended</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para>
              <text>This section amends the KiwiSaver Act 2006.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para>
              <text>The heading to <citation jurisdiction="nz"><atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="1283492" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="DLM1638164 - prov 206" atidlm:xmlId="DLM1638192" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>section 206</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="786094" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM1638192" atidlm:targetKey="2310015" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM379446" atidlm:targetName="prov 206" atidlm:sourceName="DLM1638192" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM379444.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM1584797.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Parent_id" atidlm:value="DLM1584831" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation> is amended by omitting <amend.in quote="1"><emphasis style="bold">investment advice</emphasis></amend.in> and substituting <amend.in quote="1"><emphasis style="bold">financial adviser service</emphasis></amend.in>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
